October Reads:
Blue. The Color of Noise - Cant wait to jump into Steve Aoki's memoirs. I've been a fan of his for over a decade and thankful to call him a friend now, so it's time to see the story behind the legend. Thanks @steveaoki!
Craft Coffee. A Manual - Need to step up my coffee game with hard science. Cooking really is chemistry: the combination of heat, ingredients, and senses. Going mad scientist.
Puzzle Ninja - @madeleinearthur gave this to me because of our love for riddles that we discovered we shared on set. Ive flipped through some of the sections, and not only does it give you actual puzzles, but also the history behind them and how they were developed. I find the underlying meta rules to WHY games and puzzles work more interesting than winning or finding the solution themselves... mainly because it'll help me win more in the future ðŸ™ƒ
